						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Reshaping-tertiary-agricultural-education/Related-developments/New-guidelines-call-for-broad-changes-in-science-education" title="New guidelines call for broad changes in science education" alt="link">New guidelines call for broad changes in science education</a></h2>

	
					<p>Students can become more intelligent science consumers by learning how scientific work is done: how ideas are developed and tested, what counts as strong or weak evidence, and how insights from many disciplines fit together into a coherent picture of the world.<a href="http://nyti.ms/10QTwAU" target="_self">http://nyti.ms/10QTwAU</a>(The New York Times, 09/04/2013)</p>
