						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/Reshaping-tertiary-agricultural-education/Related-developments/Are-we-losing-sight-of-the-true-value-of-research-impact" title="Are we losing sight of the true value of research ‘impact’?" alt="link">Are we losing sight of the true value of research ‘impact’?</a></h2>

	
					<p>Andrew Clappison tracks the impact of public-goods research related to international development. Relating the debates from the Future of Impact Conference (UK Higher Ed), he senses the risk of bureaucratising institutional approaches to the Research Excellence Framework that could stall innovation.<a href="http://www.researchtoaction.org/2013/04/are-we-losing-sight-of-the-true-value-of-research-impact/" target="_self">http://www.researchtoaction.org/2013/04/are-we-losing-sight-of-the-true-value-of-research-impact/</a>(Research to Action, 11/04/2013)</p>
